Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Democratic Congo 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- The famous work of Kim Jong Il "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification" was brought out in booklet by the Congo New Media Publishing House of Democratic Congo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work published on Aug. 4, Juche 86 (1997) deals with the undying exploits performed by Kim Il Sung for national reunification, formulates the three principles of national reunification, the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo as the three charters for national reunification and indicates the tasks and ways for accomplishing the cause of national reunification based on them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A book releasing ceremony was held at the publishing house on April 6.

Day of Sun Commemorated in Egypt 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- The Egypt-Korea Friendship Association released information bulletin "Great Man President Kim Il Sung" on April 11 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin said that April 15 this year is the significant Day of the Sun, the 95th birth anniversary of Kim Il Sung. It dealt with the President's ideological and theoretical and leadership exploits and his personality as the great man who impressed and fascinated all people with boundless love and noble virtues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It introduced the Juche idea and Songun idea fathered by the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the Juche idea and Songun idea, the Korean revolution has steadily advanced along the road of victory despite unprecedented adversities and complicated situation and progressive humankind came to possess a powerful ideological and theoretical weapon for national liberation and the struggle against imperialism, it said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A fresh turn has taken place in the ideological and moral life of humankind and there has begun a new era of history, the era of independence, where the popular masses hew out their destiny independently and creatively.

President of Equatorial Guinea Supports Korean People 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Obiang Nguema Mbasogo, president of Equatorial Guinea, expressed support for the Korean people in their just cause of achieving the peaceful reunification of the country by pooling the efforts of all Koreans free from outsiders' interference when he met the DPRK ambassador to Equatorial Guinea who paid a farewell call on him on April 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The president wished the Korean people fresh success in their efforts to achieve national reunification and prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that he can never forget the day when he was received by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il when visiting the DPRK 15 years ago.

Kim Il Sung Praised by Bangladesh Party Leader 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Dilip Barua, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Bangladesh (Marxist-Leninist), praised President Kim Il Sung as genuine leader of the Korean people and other revolutionary people of the world struggling for independence in his statement released on April 15 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has turned into a powerful socialist country and the socialist forces and anti-imperialist forces for independence have grown stronger in the international arena thanks to the brilliant ideological and theoretical activities and revolutionary practices of the President, he said, noting that the great exploits performed by the President in carrying out the cause of independence of the popular masses will shine long with the history of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the belief that the Songun policy pursued by Kim Jong Il, a creditable successor to the revolutionary cause of the President, will bring greater victory and glory to the Korean people and other revolutionary people of the world.

Russian International Fund Delegation Interviewed  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- The members of the delegation of the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Arts for the Century" who had participated in the unveiling ceremony of the monument "Protectors of Arts for the Century" bearing the august names of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il were interviewed by media reporters here on April 15. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Oleg Oleinik, president of the fund who was leading the delegation, said the monument "Protectors of Arts for the Century" erected in high praise of the undying exploits of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il represented reverence of the Russian people for them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As shown by the letters inscribed on the monument, the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Arts for the Century" awarded several times the supreme orders and honorary titles of the fund to the great leaders of Korea, he said, adding: This is the high appreciation of their distinguished exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pyotr Stronski, designer of the monument, said the august names of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il would be permanently inscribed on the monuments to be erected in different parts of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Experts Council of the Fund Yuri Kovelenov noted that Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il made immortal contributions to the independent and creative development of humankind and the boosting of the friendly relations between the Russian and Korean peoples. The monument "Protectors of Arts for the Century" will shine long, conveying the great feats of the leaders of Korea, he stressed.

Russian Fund Delegation Hosts Reception  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- The delegation of the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Arts for the Century" hosted a reception at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel on April 16 after the unveiling ceremony of the monument "Protectors of Arts for the Century" bearing the august names of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were Minister of Culture Kang Nung Su, Acting Chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Mun Jae Chol, Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kung Sok Ung, Director of the Mansudae Art Studio Ju Su Yong, Vice-Chairwoman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries who is chairwoman of the Korea-Russia Friendship Association Hong Son Ok and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the members of the delegation of the fund headed by its President Oleg Oleinik, Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Valery Sukhinin and staff members of his embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Performance Given by Russian Artistes  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- A performance was given by the Russian artistes participating in the 25th April Spring Friendship Art Festival at the Ponghwa Art Theater on April 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Kim Yong Nam, Ri Yong Mu, Choe Thae Bok and officials concerned and officials in the fields of literature and arts and media and working people here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also among the audience were Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Valery Sukhinin and staff members of the embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian art groups comprise many international concours winners and other famous artistes. They displayed high artistic talents in the performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance began with the chorus of the immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Il Sung" presented by artistes of the Moscow State Academy Chamber Chorus of Russia. It was conducted by Minin Vladimir, people's artiste of the Soviet Union and state prize winner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A male soloist of the famous pop singers' group of Russia who is Russian people's artiste and international concours winner presented Korean song "Attraction," successfully representing the true feelings of the Korean people and other progressives of the world entrusting both their destinies and future to Kim Jong Il, attracted by his noble personality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the "Vendelya" Folk Dance Troupe of Russia and the Tap dancers troupe of Russia staged dances "Tambourine Dance of Voronezh Region", "Semyonovna" and "Katyusha" and other numbers and the Bayan Orchestra "Ad Libitum" named after Gnesin of Russia, the "Pereprava" musical company of Russia and a famous artiste and her party of the Moscow Grand Theatre colorful numbers and world famous songs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Jong Il" was presented by artistes of the above-said chamber chorus when the atmosphere picked up in the theater. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket was conveyed to the performers and senior officials of the Party and state mounted the stage to congratulate the Russian artistes on their successful performance.

Joint Performances of Art Festival Given 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Joint performances of the 25th April Spring Friendship Art Festival were given at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre, the Pyongyang Grand Theatre and the Pyongyang Circus Theatre here on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were appreciated by senior party, army and state officials, the chairpersons of friendly parties, officials of party and power bodies, social organizations, ministries and national institutions, heroes and persons of merit and artistes and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were the heads of overseas compatriots' delegations including the delegation of Koreans in Japan, and overseas Koreans staying in the socialist homeland and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foreign artistes and overseas Korean artistes put on the stage colorful numbers including choruses and other songs, dances and instrumental music. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre was given by the artistes from China, Georgia, Germany, Mongolia, Romania, Finland, Indonesia, Uzbekistan, Australia, Egypt, Ukraine and Tajikistan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers presented immortal revolutionary hymn "Song of General Kim Il Sung", mixed duet "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il", female solo "My Beloved Country" and other numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the Pyongyang Grand Theatre the performance was given by art groups of overseas Koreans from Japan, China and the United States and an art group of the International United Confederation of Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers put on the stage such numbers as female vocal solo "Song of Loyalty", an immortal masterpiece, cello solo "The Image of the Great Man Will Be Always Remembered", dance "Longing for the Leader", male vocal solo "The General Is the Great Defender", female solos "Care of the Mother Party" and "Blue Sky over My Country", female vocal solo and pangchang "We Sing of the Country" and "We Pledge", the fourth movement of symphony "Our Leader Will Always Be with Us." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the Pyongyang Circus Theater acrobats of Russia, China, Mongolia and Ukraine presented "Aerial Stunt", "Wit of Standing on One Hand", "Two Men's Stunt", "Dexterity at Caps", "Chair Towering", "Male and Female Aerial Stunt" and other numbers, impressing the spectators with dynamic and witty techniques and refined movements.

April Spring Friendship Art Festival Successfully Goes on
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- The 25th April Spring Friendship Art Festival is going on with success in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The curtain of the first festival was raised in Pyongyang in April Juche 71 (1982) by the Japan-Korea Society for Music and Art Interchange, "Tiempo Nuevo" Art Troupe of Peru and artistes from various other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 18,000 artistes from different countries of the world have taken part in the festival so far to give over 1,500 art performances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have put on the stage the art pieces they created with deep reverence for President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, national music, dance and acrobatic pieces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Festivals had reached their acme when the President appreciated the joint performances and had photo sessions with the festival participants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though the President demised, the festival has continued in a more significant way in reflection of the ardent reverence of the world people for him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage of the festival for the year of Juche 91 (2002) were colorful numbers that world-famous art troupes from China, Russia, Egypt, Mongolia, Italy, Rumania and other countries had prepared with sincerity to commemorate the 90th birth anniversary of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Foreign artistes sing "Song of General Kim Il Sung" in praise of the undying exploits performed by the President in the efforts for the people's cause of independence, the cause of socialism in his life-time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The current festival attended by famous art troupes and stars of many countries will contribute to deepening the friendship and strengthening cultural cooperation and exchange between the nations as an international art one, thus constituting a brilliant chapter in the festival history.

Pleasure Ground Newly Built in Mangyongdae
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- A pleasure ground on Konyu Islet in Mangyongdae has been built to be opened to the public on the occasion of the significant Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The islet is located on the River Taedong near Mangyong Hill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The islet is a historical place associated with patriotic activities of Kim Ung U, great-grandfather of President Kim Il Sung, who participated in the battle for sinking the U.S. aggressors' ship General Sherman, and grandfather Kim Po Hyon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The total area of the pleasure ground covers 17 hectares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floating bridge is laid between Tongrim Pier and Konyu Islet so that the visitors to Mangyongdae may relax themselves in the ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cars can go in and out freely through the bridge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 20,000 trees of good species were newly transplanted in the pleasure ground, resembling a forest.  There are facilities for playing sport and folk amusement games including basketball, volleyball, Korean wrestling, Korean chess and yut and a boating ground in the pleasure ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are open-air tables set up in various places.  The holiday-makers can enjoy a pleasant meal time, viewing the landscape of the river banks as if they are on a sightseeing boat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is conspicuous in the pleasure ground is a large artificial pond and angling site.
 Visitors may angle for carp and silver carp at the angling site and cook the fishes caught by themselves according to their appetite. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An open-air stage for performance of art pieces is seen in the wood of aspen trees.

Friendly Joint Meeting Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- A friendly joint meeting with the delegations and delegates of the Juche idea study organizations was held in Mt. Myohyang on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were the director-general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea and delegations and delegates of the Juche idea study organizations from different countries on the visit to the DPRK on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman and members of the Korean Social Scientists Society were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vishwanath, director-general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, said that superb scenic Mt. Myohyang is associated with deep loving care of President Kim Il Sung, adding that it is a duty of the Juche idea followers to glorify his undying exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 M. Jahangir Khan, advisor of the Bangladesh Barisal Society for the Study of Songun Policy, recited in deep emotion the poem written in praise of the feats of Kim Il Sung who fathered the great Juche idea. And members of the delegation of the Mongolian Mt. Paektu Association for Independent Development sang immortal classic "Nostalgia", making the participants in the meeting excited with reverence for the great man.

Talks between DPRK and Russian Parliamentary Groups Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- Talks were held between the delegation of the DPRK-Russia friendship parliamentary group of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK and the delegation of the Russia-DPRK friendship parliamentary group of the State Duma of Russia at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on April 17. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the talks from the DPRK side were the members of the DPRK delegation headed by Hong So Hon, chairman of the DPRK-Russia friendship parliamentary group, and from the Russian side the members of the Russian delegation led by Chairman of the group Chilgichi Chimit Ondar and Valentin Chekulaev, councilor of the Russian embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on the issue of boosting the friendly ties between the two parliaments and on matters of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere.

Foreign Delegations and Delegates Here 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the International Liaison Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China led by Deputy Head Liu Hongcai arrived here today by air. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also arriving on the same day were a delegation of the Regional Office for South-East Asia of the World Health Organization led by Director Samlee Plianbangchang and delegations and delegates from Nepal, East Timor, Maldives, Myanmar, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Indonesia, India and Thailand to participate in the WHO Southeast Asian Regional Consultation on Strengthening Health Systems through PHC Approach.

Friendly Meeting with Members of Indonesian Embassy Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- The Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and the Korea-Indonesia Friendship Association arranged a friendly meeting with members of the Indonesian embassy here at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on April 17 on the occasion of the 42nd anniversary of the historic visit Kim Jong Il paid to Indonesia, accompanying President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Ambassador Daulat Hotma Audison Passaribu and members of the Indonesian embassy here and members of the Indonesian Guruhsukarno Dancing Troupe participating in the 25th April Spring Friendship Art Festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jon Yong Jin, chairman of the Korea-Indonesia Friendship Association who is vice-chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and others were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers at the meeting said that the visit Kim Jong Il paid to Indonesia, accompanying Kim Il Sung, was a historic event which opened a new chapter of the Korea-Indonesia friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They expressed belief that the long-standing friendly relations between the two countries would grow stronger in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the meeting enjoyed an art performance given by schoolchildren of Korea-Indonesia Friendship Pyongyang Ryulgok Middle School, talked to one another about the need to boost the bilateral cooperative relations and sang songs and danced, deepening the friendship.

Overseas Koreans Feted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- There was a banquet at the People's Palace of Culture on April 16, which was arranged by Kim Jong Il for overseas Koreans on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were the delegation of Koreans in Japan, the delegation of veteran officials of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), the delegation of Chongryon officials, the delegation of the General Association of Koreans in China, the delegation of the Federation of Koreans in the United States, the delegation of the International United Confederation of Koreans, the delegation of the Federation of Koreans in Australia, the delegation of the Central Association of Korean Nationals in Russia, the delegation of the Federation of Koreans in New Zealand and other overseas Koreans' delegations and visiting groups and overseas Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Ki Nam and Director of the Agency of Service for Overseas Compatriots of Korea Kim Yu Ho and other officials concerned were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Ki Nam in his speech said the undying exploits of Generalissimo Kim Il Sung who enjoyed undisputed reverence of the whole world as the veteran statesman in the era of independence are now shining all the brighter today thanks to Kim Jong Il who is identical to the Generalissimo in idea, leadership and virtues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the belief that the compatriots overseas would hold President Kim Il Sung in high esteem through all ages as the eternal sun of the nation, dynamically push forward the reunification movement under the banner of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and realizing unity under the leadership of Kim Jong Il and achieve proud results in the patriotic movement for building a great prosperous powerful socialist country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon and head of the delegation of Koreans in Japan, in his speech said the Koreans overseas would resolutely defend the patriotic tradition and legacy left over by Kim Il Sung and fully defend and uphold the Songun policy of Kim Jong Il, the true policy of love for the country, the nation and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will devote our all to the accomplishment of the worthy cause of the country's reunification and the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, keeping pace with the home people recording a chronicle of fresh prosperity of socialist Korea in the spirit of Thaechon, he said.

Kim Jong Il Sends Educational Aid Fund and Stipends to Korean Children in Japan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 17 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il sent educational aid fund and stipends amounting to 238,000,000 yen to the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) for the democratic national education of the children of Koreans in Japan on the occasion of the 95th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The educational aid funds and stipends sent so far by Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il to Chongryon in 153 installments total 46,006,223,000 yen.

Congo Democratico: obra de Kim Jong Il en folleto
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 17 de abril (ATCC) -- La Editorial "Congo New Media" del Congo Democratico dio a luz en folleto la obra maestra del Dirigente Kim Jong Il "Materialicemos de modo consecuente el legado del gran lider, camarada Kim Il Sung para la reunificacion de la patria", publicada el 4 de agosto del 86 (1997) de la Era Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta obra da cuenta de las hazanas inmortales del Presidente Kim Il Sung realizadas por la causa de reunificacion de la patria y formula como 3 cartas para la misma causa los 3 principios de la reunificacion de la patria, el programa de diez puntos de la gran unidad pannacional y el proyecto de la fundacion de la Republica Federal Democratica de Coryo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Igualmente, a base de ello, aclara las tareas y los medios para cumplir la causa en cuestion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La ceremonia de edicion de la obra tuvo lugar el dia 6 en la entidad arriba mencionada.

Funciones conjuntas del XXV Festival Artistico de Amistad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 17 de abril (ATCC) -- Tuvieron lugar la vispera en el Gran Teatro de Pyongyang, el de Pyongyang Este y el Circo de Pyongyang las funciones conjuntas en el marco del XXV Festival Artistico de Amistad Abril en Primavera. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Las vieron los cuadros del partido, el ejercito y el Estado, presidentes de partidos amigos, funcionarios de instituciones del partido y el Poder, organizaciones sociales, ministerios y organos centrales, heroes, personas ameritadas, artistas y trabajadores capitalinos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Ademas, las vieron los jefes de las delegaciones de coreanos residentes en ultramar, que se encuentran de visita en la patria socialista, inclusive el jefe de la delegacion de coreanos residentes en Japon, y otros compatriotas y huespedes extranjeros. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Los artistas de varios paises y los coreanos residentes radicados ultramar presentaron este dia variados programas como coros, canciones, bailes y musicas instrumentales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En el Gran Teatro de Pyongyang Este actuaron los artistas de China, Georgia, Alemania, Mongolia, Rumania, Finlandia, Indonesia, Uzbekistan, Australia, Egipto, Ucrania y Tadjikistan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Ellos pusieron en la escena el inmortal himno revolucionario "Cancion del general Kim Il Sung", el duo mixto "Himno al camarada Kim Jong Il", el solo femenino "Mi querida patria", etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El Gran Teatro de Pyongyang fue escenario de los conjuntos artisticos de coreanos residentes en Japon, China y EE.UU. y el de la Asociacion Internacional de los Coreanos (Unidad). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Los ejecutantes compatriotas ofrecieron la obra maestra "Cancion de fidelidad" en el solo femenino, "Sera eterna esa grandiosa imagen" en solo de violonchelo, "Anorando al Lider" en el baile, "General es gran defensor" en solo masculino, "El regazo del partido madre" y "Cielo azul de mi pais" en solos femeninos, "Cantamos de la patria" en solo femenino y Pangchang (coro del foso) y "Juramos", cuarto movimiento de la sinfonia "El Lider siempre estara con nosotros", entre otros programas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Mientras tanto, en el Circo de Pyongyang los acrobatas de Rusia, China, Mongolia y Ucrania mostraron espectaculares episodios en varias piezas tales como "figuras corporales en el aire", "parado de cabeza sosteniendose con una mano", "figuras acrobaticas de 2 hombres", "habilidad con gorras", "apilamiento de sillas" y "figuras corporales de una pareja".
